==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superpose
<hw>Su`per*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Superposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Superposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>superposer</ets>. See <er>Super-</er>, and <er>Pose</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To lay upon, as one kind of rock on another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>To lay (a figure) upon another in
such a manner that all the parts of the one coincide with the parts of
the other; <as>as, to <ex>superpose</ex> one plane figure on
another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superposition</ent>⟦br⟧
